-        <section id="delegated-operational-control">
-          <h3>🔸 Delegated Operational Control</h3>
-          <p>
-            The
-            <span style="font-style: italic">active operational figure</span>,
-            who holds no formal title, is the legal cofounder’s partner. She
-            manages onboarding, team scheduling, and
-            <span style="font-style: italic">de facto</span> HR — without any
-            documented delegation or reporting line.
-          </p>
-          <p>
-            <mark style="background-color: #e0e0e0"
-              >Her authority rests on routine presence and behavioral dominance,
-              not formal role definition.</mark
-            >
-          </p>
-          <p>
-            In practice, she relies on a
-            <span style="font-weight: bold">triad of N–1 figures</span> — floor
-            manager, bar manager, sous-chefs, and head chef — to coordinate
-            daily activity.
-            <u>Direct contact with the wider team is avoided by design.</u>
-          </p>
-          <p>
-            <mark style="background-color: #e0e0e0"
-              >No internal org chart, hierarchy, or substitution mechanism was
-              identified.</mark
-            >
-            Authority appears situational, relational, and hard to replicate
-            without her personal presence.
-          </p>
-        </section>
-        <p>
-          “In certain cases — where strong operational ethics or
-          disproportionate accountability is observed — advisory rates may be
-          adapted accordingly.”
-        </p>
