-              <span style="color: #555"
-                >→ No clear registry = no audit trail = perception of agility
-                but loss of control</span
-              ><br />
-              🔺 Organizational drift: due to long-term registry opacity (R01s),
-              no clear staff hierarchy is maintained; accountability <br />
-              <dissolves class="br"></dissolves>
-              <br />
-              <strong>R01s — Structural Opacity on Workforce Supervision</strong
-              ><br />
-              ↳ <strong>R01L</strong> — No documented scope of duties, undefined
-              supervision chain<br />
-              ⤷→ <strong>R01s.1</strong> — Absence of onboarding protocol<br />
-              ➤ <strong>Ambiguity of responsibility:</strong> unclear task
-              boundaries, non-explicit chain of command, blurred reporting
-              lines.<br />
-              <span style="color: red">▲</span>
-              <strong>Strategic underdefinition:</strong> flou structurel used
-              to maintain narrative flexibility, prevent traceability, and
-              discourage escalation. Breeds passive instability and weakens
-              internal cohesion.
-
-              <br />
-
-              → <u>Absence of onboarding protocol</u>: no documented scope of
-              duties or supervision chain.<br />
-              🔻 <strong>Procedural ambiguity</strong>: potential misattribution
-              of liability in case of incident or internal complaint. <br />
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <strong
-                >Strategic misalignment risk due to lack of high-end F&B
-                industry insight</strong
-              ><br />
-              → Quan’s positioning depends on a deep understanding of the
-              integration of branded F&B experiences into the luxury hospitality
-              industry. The neo-fusion concept, as industrialized by successful
-              chef-led brands, functions only when aligned with fine dining
-              standards and hospitality-driven service models. Recruiting
-              leadership without this awareness risks degrading both brand
-              identity and future scalability.
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <strong
-                >Narrative incoherence due to culturally misaligned
-                leadership</strong
-              ><br />
-              → Replacing the founders with two visibly non-Asian Swedish
-              figures could fracture the perceived legitimacy of the brand.
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <strong>Loss of local anchoring in recruitment</strong><br />
-              → Disconnect from Malmö's F&B microeconomy weakens performance and
-              credibility
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <strong>No assignable leadership</strong><br />
-              → Impossible to re-delegate without audit or formal reset
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <strong>Contagion risk to other units</strong><br />
-              → Normalization of governance opacity
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <strong>Loyalty fragmentation</strong><br />
-              → Team divided, trust erosion, potential leak of internal tensions
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <strong>Risk of governance masking margin manipulation</strong
-              ><br />
-              → Cost-saving schemes disguised as restructuring may inflate
-              EBITDA artificially
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <strong
-                >Risk of vertical escalation in absence of internal conflict
-                buffer</strong
-              ><br />
-              → Without a legitimate and recognized authority to absorb
-              field-level tensions, grievances may bypass local structures and
-              reach corporate leadership, legal teams, or external entities
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <strong>Loss of traction due to quality dilution</strong><br />
-              → Perceived decline in service or product quality may dissolve
-              rare positioning and reset customer expectations
-            </li>
-          </ul>
