-      <main class="main-content">
-        <section id="violation-cases" style="margin-top: 3em">
-          <h2>🧱 Structural Violations — Selected Cases</h2>
-          <p>
-            Below are five emblematic cases of
-            <strong>structural and ethical violations</strong> that triggered
-            the ripple effect. Each item is derived from internal communication,
-            often archived in full, and serves as a live case study in
-            <em
-              >delegated opacity, displaced accountability, and reputational
-              fragility</em
-            >.
-          </p>
-
-          <div class="legal-case">
-            <h2>🧭 Case #1/5 — Police Threat in Response to Salary Claim</h2>
-
-            <p>
-              <strong>Date:</strong> January 26, 2025<br />
-              <strong>Sender:</strong> <code>se@quanbyquan.se</code><br />
-              <strong>Topic:</strong> Unpaid salary, missing contract, unpaid
-              overtime<br />
-              <strong>Response:</strong> Employer threatens police report after
-              formal salary request
-            </p>
-
-            <hr />
-
-            <p>
-              <strong>⚠️ Excerpt (direct quote):</strong><br />
-              <em
-                ><a
-                  href=" https://drive.google.com/file/d/1i7BX_Itwg-C86M8BueRpq2annGUoBqeh/view?usp=drive_link"
-                  class="file-link"
-                  >"You are frightening me and I’m thinking of doing a police
-                  report on you.”</a
-                ></em
-              >
-            </p>
-
-            <hr />
-
-            <p>
-              <strong>📌 Context</strong><br />
-              Following multiple unanswered messages requesting salary payment
-              and documentation, a formal email was sent on January 26, 2025.<br />
-              The email clearly outlined:
-            </p>
-            <ul>
-              <li>
-                an <strong>unpaid salary</strong> for work performed from Nov 23
-                to Dec 15
-              </li>
-              <li>
-                a <strong>missing payslip and contract</strong>, despite
-                repeated demands
-              </li>
-              <li>
-                <strong>unrecorded overtime</strong>, particularly in the final
-                two weeks
-              </li>
-            </ul>
-            <p>
-              The employer’s direct response was not a clarification, but an
-              <strong>explicit mention of involving the police</strong>.
-            </p>
-
-            <hr />
-
-            <p>
-              <strong>🔍 Strategic Signal</strong><br />
-              This message was immediately flagged under:
-            </p>
-            <ul>
-              <li>
-                <a href="#Narrative-Resistance" class="note-link"
-                  >Narrative Resistance</a
-                >
-                — attempt to <em>reframe a lawful claim as aggression</em>
-              </li>
-              <li>
-                <a href="#Symbolic-Reversal" class="note-link"
-                  >Symbolic Reversal</a
-                >
-                — <em>ethical inversion</em> of roles: victim framed as threat
-              </li>
-              <li>
-                <a href="#Read-and-Recept-Clause" class="note-link"
-                  >Read and Receipt Clause™</a
-                >
-                — <em>triggered</em>
-              </li>
-            </ul>
-
-            <hr />
-          </div>
-
-          <section>
-            <h2>🧾 Case #2 — Delegated Blame and Payment Panic</h2>
-
-            <p>
-              <strong>Date:</strong> January 28, 2025<br />
-              <strong>Sender:</strong> se@quanbyquan.se, hs@quanbyquan.se<br />
-              <strong>Topic:</strong> Delayed salary payment, improper payment
-              method, missing payslips<br />
-              <strong>Response:</strong> Employer first deflects responsibility,
-              then shifts it to a subordinate.
-            </p>
-
-            <hr />
-
-            <p>
-              <strong>⚠️ Excerpt (direct quote):</strong><br />
-              <em>“Your payment has been made on time. STOP harassing me!”</em>
-              — Sahar Elnasser<br />
-              <em>“This is the fastest way to resolve the matter.”</em> — Henrik
-              Siebert
-            </p>
-
-            <hr />
-
-            <h3>📎 Context</h3>
-            <p>
-              After escalating his formal request on January 26, the claimant
-              received a brief and hostile reply from Ms. Elnasser, followed
-              within hours by a minimalistic technical reply from Mr. Siebert.
-            </p>
-
-            <ul>
-              <li>
-                The response did not address <strong>unpaid overtime</strong> or
-                <strong>missing payslips</strong>.
-              </li>
-              <li>
-                Instead, payment was made via
-                <strong>unannounced postal checks</strong> without prior
-                instruction — a method considered outdated and impractical.
-              </li>
-              <li>
-                Henrik Siebert confirmed the payment with two reference numbers
-                and advised to use Swedbank’s online platform.
-              </li>
-            </ul>
-
-            <p>
-              The responsibility shift, from a panicked superior to a calmer
-              subordinate, implicitly designated Mr. Siebert as the accountable
-              legal interface.
-            </p>
-
-            <hr />
-
-            <h3>🔍 Strategic Signal</h3>
-            <p>This exchange triggered:</p>
-            <ul>
-              <li>
-                <a href="#" class="note-link">Delegated Opacity</a> — senior
-                actor refuses to engage directly, pushing responsibility
-                downward
-              </li>
-              <li>
-                <a href="#" class="note-link">Silent Substitution</a> — chain of
-                command reassigns interface without acknowledgment
-              </li>
-              <li>
-                <a href="#" class="note-link">Cryptographic History Clause™</a>
-                — enforced via documented timestamps and delivery method
-              </li>
-            </ul>
-          </section>
-
-          <h3>📩 Failure to Acknowledge Legal Identity or Mandate</h3>
-          <ul>
-            <li>
-              Multiple requests for clarification of contract terms, identity of
-              the legal employer, and responsible party were met with silence.
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              This vacuum <strong>invalidated trust channels</strong> and
-              constituted <em>opacity-by-design</em>.
-            </li>
-          </ul>
-
-          <h3>📜 Final Legal Demand Letter — Refusal to Engage</h3>
-          <ul>
-            <li>
-              Upon receiving a clear and structured legal letter, the company
-              replied with
-              <em
-                >no recognition of role, only retroactive transactional
-                payment</em
-              >.
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              This became the <strong>symbolic ignition point</strong> —
-              confirming that structural negligence would be met with structural
-              exposure.
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <a
-                href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1j_yyQmsELeOgqia1I6lGyMHIDclzE4xB/view?usp=sharing"
-                class="file-link"
-                >Original Demand Letter (PDF)</a
-              >
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <a
-                href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1YUFw5uQpJin4YjZRbFMMdBwF3djMiI5R/view?usp=sharing"
-                class="file-link"
-                >Official Response (PDF)</a
-              >
-            </li>
-          </ul>
-        </section>
-        <section id="origin-letter" style="margin-top: 3em">
-          <h2>📎 Origin Document — Symbolic Trigger</h2>
-          <p
-            style="background-color: #e0e0e0; padding: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em"
-          >
-            This section contains the original
-            <strong>legal demand letter</strong> sent by the agent — then acting
-            as a dishwasher in a subcontracted unit — followed by the official
-            response received. These two documents together
-            <em>constitute the symbolic ignition point</em> of the
-            <strong>Ripple Effect</strong> and frame the legitimacy of the role.
-          </p>
-          <p>
-            The letter was sent after repeated operational violations, including
-            <strong
-              >non-payment, contractual opacity, and unacknowledged
-              status</strong
-            >
-            within the group. The response received offered a retroactive salary
-            payment equivalent to two weeks, without acknowledging any of the
-            claims.
-          </p>
-          <blockquote
-            style="
-              border-left: 4px solid #888;
-              margin: 1em 0;
-              padding-left: 1em;
-            "
-          >
-            "This document constitutes the point of origin for all strategic
-            developments to follow. It encapsulates the dissonance between
-            field-level suffering and board-level silence."
-          </blockquote>
-          <p>
-            As such, it becomes the first proof of strategic negligence — and
-            <strong>a durable marker of asymmetry</strong>. Its inclusion here
-            is not to reopen conflict, but to trace the architecture of the role
-            back to its ethical root.
-          </p>
-          <ul>
-            <li>
-              <a
-                href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1j_yyQmsELeOgqia1I6lGyMHIDclzE4xB/view?usp=sharing"
-                class="file-link"
-                >Original Demand Letter (PDF)</a
-              >
-            </li>
-            <li>
-              <a
-                href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/1YUFw5uQpJin4YjZRbFMMdBwF3djMiI5R/view?usp=sharing"
-                class="file-link"
-                >Official Response (PDF)</a
-              >
-            </li>
-          </ul>
-        </section>
-
-        <section id="note-origin" style="margin-top: 2em">
-          <h2>🗂 Note — Structural Origin</h2>
-          <p>
-            The Ripple Effect was not initiated from abstraction — it was born
-            of lived experience and
-            <strong>strategic failure at the periphery</strong>. The triggering
-            moment: a dishwasher, unpaid and unrecognized, legally demanding
-            visibility. The group’s response was minimal, transactional, and
-            systemically blind.
-          </p>
-          <p>
-            From this point emerged a conviction:
-            <em
-              >no operational reform is credible unless it emerges from the
-              overlooked edge.</em
-            >
-          </p>
-          <p>
-            This note marks the
-            <strong>ethical and narrative foundation</strong> of the
-            architecture that follows. It must be understood not as anecdote,
-            but as <strong>precursor structure</strong>.
-          </p>
-        </section>
